 {"id":"bd-23l","title":"Task: Implement FlashRank nano reranker via ONNX","description":"## Task: Implement FlashRank nano reranker via ONNX (baseline-only unless eligible)

### IMPORTANT
FlashRank nano is pre-2025-11 unless a new post-2025-10 variant exists in
reranker_candidates_2025_11+.json. If not eligible, treat as baseline-only.

## Purpose
Provide a speed/quality baseline for reranking. FlashRank nano is a ~4MB
cross-encoder distilled from larger models, using ONNX for inference.

## Architecture
```rust
pub struct FlashRankReranker {
    session: ort::Session,
    tokenizer: tokenizers::Tokenizer,
    max_length: usize,  // 512 tokens typical
    name: String,
}

impl Reranker for FlashRankReranker {
    fn rerank(&self, query: &str, documents: &[&str]) -> Result<Vec<f32>> {
        // Cross-encoder: each (query, doc) pair is encoded together
        let mut scores = Vec::with_capacity(documents.len());

        // Batch encode all pairs for efficiency
        let pairs: Vec<_> = documents.iter()
            .map(|doc| (query, *doc))
            .collect();

        // Tokenize pairs with [SEP] separator
        for chunk in pairs.chunks(32) { // Batch size 32
            let encodings: Vec<_> = chunk.iter()
                .map(|(q, d)| {
                    self.tokenizer.encode((*q, *d), true)
                        .map(|e| e.truncate(self.max_length, 0))
                })
                .collect::<Result<Vec<_>>>()?;

            // Prepare ONNX inputs: input_ids, attention_mask, token_type_ids
            let batch_size = encodings.len();
            let max_len = encodings.iter().map(|e| e.len()).max().unwrap_or(0);

            let input_ids = build_padded_tensor(&encodings, max_len, 0);
            let attention_mask = build_attention_mask(&encodings, max_len);
            let token_type_ids = build_type_ids(&encodings, max_len);

            // Run ONNX inference
            let outputs = self.session.run(ort::inputs![
                "input_ids" => input_ids,
                "attention_mask" => attention_mask,
                "token_type_ids" => token_type_ids,
            ]?)?;

            // Extract logits → sigmoid → score
            let logits = outputs[0].extract_tensor::<f32>()?;
            for i in 0..batch_size {
                let score = sigmoid(logits[[i, 0]]);
                scores.push(score);
            }
        }

        Ok(scores)
    }

    fn model_name(&self) -> &str { &self.name }
    fn max_length(&self) -> usize { self.max_length }
}

fn sigmoid(x: f32) -> f32 { 1.0 / (1.0 + (-x).exp()) }
```

## Model Files
- Model: model.onnx (~4MB for nano variant)
- Tokenizer: tokenizer.json
- Config: config.json (max_length, label mapping)
- Cache path: ~/.cache/xf/models/flashrank-nano/

## Key Considerations
- Cross-encoder: O(n) forward passes for n documents (not parallelizable across docs without batching)
- Batch size 32: balances throughput vs memory
- Truncation: long docs truncated to max_length tokens (512)
- Score interpretation: sigmoid output in [0, 1]
- For top-100 reranking: ~3 batches of 32 + 1 batch of 4
- Expected latency: 50-200ms for 100 documents on CPU

